* Chores

  * Replace NodeManager with a ClusterLayout that owns both the live
    topology view and a background monitor task to keep the local cluster
    layout cache refreshed. DiscoveryService becomes a pure query object.

    The connection pool now no longer interacts directly with the cluster layout
    on the request path and simply accepts any ClusterNodeLocation when a
    connection is requested and manages that connection in a subpool.
    Periodically a garbage collection task will remove any sub pools (and connections
    that are in the pool) that no longer exist in the cluster layout.

    Any "querying" for nodes by clients (regular client, pipeline, pubsub etc) should
    only use the cluster_layout attribute of the connection pool directly.

    The ClusterLayout instance is owned by the connection pool since it uses
    the connection pools task group to run its monitor task and the monitor task's
    lifecycle is somewhat logically tied to that of the connection pool.
